
[1]besayle

   BESA'YLE, n. A great grandfather.

   If the abatement happened on the death of one's grandfather or
   grandmother, a writ of ayle lieth; if on the death of the great
   grandfather, then a writ of besayle; but if it mounts one degree
   higher, to the tresayle, or grandfather's grandfather, &c.,the writ is
   called a writ of cosinage, or de consanguineo.
